[[File:MountedLavaLizardHeart.png|thumb|right|A tanray heart crystal]]
{{Quote|It is a fabulous crystal formed under intense heat and pressure that is...well, it is shaped like the heart of a tanray. They can be worth a hefty sum to certain collectors, but most people just use them as decoration.|Surveyor [[Jo Keslev]]|<ref name="SWG:ToOW">''[[Star Wars Galaxies: Trials of Obi-Wan]]''</ref>}}
'''Tanray heart crystals''', also known as '''lava lizard hearts''', were a type of [[Crystal/Legends|crystal]] found on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Mustafar/Legends|Mustafar]]. Formed under the intense heat and pressure of the [[Magma/Legends|lava]] world, the end product resembled the [[Heart/Legends|heart]] of the [[tanray]], hence its name.

Sometime following the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] in [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], surveyor [[Jo Keslev]] gave a [[Spacer/Legends|spacer]] one of these crystals as a reward for activating all the markers he had placed in regions across Mustafar. This particular tanray heart crystal was mounted on a [[Color/Legends|black]] base, so that it could be displayed as a trophy.

